This paper discusses the impact of blood rheology on wall shear stress in a computational model of the middle cerebral artery. The study involves computational fluid dynamics and the analysis of rheology models, which are relevant to the fields of computational engineering (cs.CE) and biomedical engineering (cs.BM). The paper also discusses the use of the three-band diagram analysis, which is a method used in the study of fluid mechanics and could be relevant to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper involves the comparison of computational results to experimentally observed pathological thresholds, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational medicine (cs.CM).
